commit.message:
Add optional timeout argument to open and open_simple

While 'search' accepts a timeout option, 'open' and 'open_simple' do not.
This is a problem if there is a network failure; 'open' can hang for a
long time.

That might be fine for small scripts and such, but for production
services, being able to bound how long your service will wait for a
connection before giving up is essential.
avoid build with incompatible numeric types

Add scope="subtree" to search example

I was also bitten by trying to get this working based on the example code and wondering what I'd done wrong...

src/lualdap.c: fix search with multiple attrs

Fix segfault in search when using an attrs table with more than one attr
follow mkdocs, site_url is now required
